  • Package <Unnamed>

    • Class ImageRotatorGUI extends javax.swing.JPanel implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • angleSlider

          javax.swing.JSlider angleSlider
          The JSlider angleSlider is used to set the angle of rotation.

        • continueBox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox continueBox
          The JCheckBox continueBox is used to implement the functionality of the GUI by allowing for continual rotation. See ImageRotatorGUI for detailed explaination.

        • speedSlider

          javax.swing.JSlider speedSlider
          The JSlider speedSlider is used to set the clock between 1 sec and 10 milisec.

        • stopBox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox stopBox
          The JCheckBox stopBox is used to implement the functionality of the GUI by allowing the user to lock in the desired angle of rotation. See ImageRotatorGUI for detailed explanation.

        • timer

          javax.swing.Timer timer
          The Timer timer is the clock used to control the speed by setting the refresh of the image. The timer is initially set to 1 sec but can be lowered down to 10ms.

        • transformA

          java.awt.geom.AffineTransform transformA
          The AffineTransform transformA is used to allow an image to be rotated a number of degrees. The AffineTransform is commonly used to rotate images and has a matrix associated with it to perform an image translation.
